verse.lines:
{lang-eng}The clouds may go and come,
And storms may sweep my sky;
This blood-sealed friendship changes not,
The Cross is ever nigh.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}I change, He changes not;
The Christ can never die;
His love, not mine, the resting-place,
His truth, not mine, the tie.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}The Cross still stands unchanged,
Though heaven is now His home;
The mighty stone is rolled away,
But yonder is His tomb!{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}I know He liveth now
At God’s right hand above;
I know the throne on which He sits,
I know His truth and love!{/lang-eng}
